h2.heading.heading--secondary#floating Floating action button
p.paragraph.
  The floating action button consists of an icon only, it can't contain a label. This type of button is used to represent an action that is important and ubiquitous.

.example
  .example__header
    .example__device-selection
      .example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--mobile
      .example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--tablet
      .example__device-selection__device.example__device-selection__device--desktop.is-active
  .example__content.example__content--centered
    iframe.example__iframe
    .example__html(data-example-centered)
      .button.button--floating.icon.icon--feedback
.toggle
  .toggle__button.icon.icon--source(data-info, data-target='#code-3') See code
  .toggle__content#code-3
    .tab-panel
      .tab-panel__header
        .tab-panel__header__tabs
          .tab-panel__header__tab.is-active HTML
          .tab-panel__header__tab LESS
      .tab-panel__content
        .tab-panel__content__tab.is-active
          ul.checklist
            li.checklist__item Do not add any whitespace within the button since it would miss-position the icon
          
          .tab-panel__content__tab__fullwidth-content
            .highlight: pre.highlight__listing.hljs: code.js
              :highlight
                <div class="button button--floating icon icon--feedback" ><div>

        .tab-panel__content__tab
          p.paragraph.
            Use the CSS classes mentioned in the HTML tab
            as mixins.
h3.heading.heading--tertiary UX Checklist
ul.checklist
  li.checklist__item Avoid this type of button for destructive actions like delete, nonspecific actions, alerts or errors.

